    {
      "id": "assistant-1774888912221-e3gy0p",
      "role": "assistant",
      "text": "I’ve written all 10 keyframe sidecar prompts.\n\nThe prompts are tuned to keep the piece emotionally restrained and visually coherent:\n- **SHOT-01** stays wide and observational\n- **SHOT-02** moves into the panda’s vulnerability\n- **SHOT-03** gives the psychologist calm, grounded presence\n- **SHOT-04** tightens for the moment of self-recognition\n- **SHOT-05** reunites them in a warmer shared frame\n\nI also kept the prompts aligned with the approved character references and made each one point back to the relevant storyboard panel, so the frames should track the board closely instead of drifting into generic therapy-scene imagery.\n\nThe next real step is to generate the keyframe images and review them before we lock motion planning. Pay closest attention to:\n- panda face and body consistency across shots\n- office layout continuity\n- whether the tone stays sincere instead of gaggy\n- whether the push from wide to intimate feels gradual and clean\n\nOnce those frames look right, I’d move straight into planning the shot manifest with durations and transitions."
    },
