      "id": "assistant-1774902883186-2mxtpe",
      "role": "assistant",
      "text": "I’ve planned the shot manifest for all 5 shots.\n\nThe rhythm is clean and restrained:\n- **SHOT-01** opens in stillness to establish the room\n- **SHOT-02** cuts closer while preserving continuity for the confession\n- **SHOT-03** reverses naturally to the psychologist\n- **SHOT-04** stays continuous but tightens to mark the internal turn\n- **SHOT-05** carries that emotional state forward and resolves into a shared frame\n\nI set them all to **4 seconds** for now, which is a solid default for this kind of dialogue-driven, performance-first scene. The transition logic is all **continuity** after the opening, so the sequence should feel like one calm conversation rather than a set of disconnected clips.\n\nNext I’d move straight into writing the shot sidecar prompts for video generation, using the approved keyframes as the motion anchors."
